Date of Birth: November 13, 1952<br/>
Birthplace: Salt Lake City, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: October 3, 2015<br/>
<br/>
Born on November 13, 1952, in Salt Lake City, Utah. Married Ruth Lybbert in June of 1977. Received his B.A. and M.D. degrees from the University of Utah, Elder Renlund received further medical and research training at Johns Hopkins Hospital. He was a Professor of Medicine at the University of Utah and the Medical Director of the Utah Transplantation Affiliated Hospitals (UTAH) Cardiac Transplant Program.
Named a member of the First Quorum of the Seventy on April 4, 2009 and served as the president of the Africa Southeast Area. 
Sustained as an Apostle in the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles on October 3, 2015.